2026-04-21 02:38:14 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['All switch indicator LEDs in Control Modules 1-8'] hypothesis_explanation="The circuit is designed such that each control module indicator (switch indicator) LED and its resistor forms a path for current across the switch. With all switches ON, the removal of each control module's indicator LED results in an open circuit at that point (since the LEDs are not bypassed, the circuit is interrupted). As the system is wired in series, these open circuits prevent any current from reaching the load, so the load lamp cannot turn on. The only LED that is on is the one in the power supply module (which is wired in parallel to the supply and independent of the series path). The lack of indicator LEDs (and the fact they cannot be replaced as stated) explains the total absence of downstream current."
